<p>For the physical computing midterm project I worked in collaboration with Keunjung Bae. The assignment was Halloween themed, so we decided to build a device that allows one to search for the spirits stuck between worlds. Inspired by technology used by the ghost hunting communities (namely <a href="https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Ghost_box" target="__blanl" class="underlined">ghost boxes</a>,) we came up with our own interface for finding ghosts.</p>

<figure>
  <img class="" style="" src="/assets/images/blog/2019-11-01-ghost-box/3.png" alt="Ghost box side view, with headphones attached." />
  <figcaption>
    Ghost box side view, with headphones attached.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>We chose a dark, mysterious look for the box, so we chose glossy acrylic as the main fabrication material. Using the illusion technique called <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pepper%27s_ghost" target="__blank" class="underlined">Pepperâ€™s Ghost</a> (so many ghosts!,) we display a visualization of the spirit search frequency spectrum as a hologram on the box screen.</p>

<figure>
  <video src="/assets/images/blog/2019-11-01-ghost-box/first.mp4" preload="" controls="" loop="" alt="Turning on the ghost box."></video>
  <figcaption>
    Turning on the ghost box.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Using a knob, the user explores the frequency spectrum and, eventually, reaches a few spirits.</p>

<figure>
  <video src="/assets/images/blog/2019-11-01-ghost-box/mid.mp4" preload="" controls="" loop="" alt="Exploring the frequency spectrum."></video>
  <figcaption>
    Exploring the frequency spectrum.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Sonically, the white noise sounds coming out of the box are produced by an <a href="https://www.sparkfun.com/datasheets/Wireless/General/TEA5767.pdf" target="__blank" class="underlined">FM Radio Receiver</a> which jumps between different frequencies a few times a second.</p>

<figure>
  <video src="/assets/images/blog/2019-11-01-ghost-box/last.mp4" preload="" controls="" loop="" alt="Turning off the ghost box."></video>
  <figcaption>
    Turning off the ghost box.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

